7 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 138 IS CREATED TO
8 READ AS FOLLOWS:
9 (1) On and after July 1, 2027, a state wholesale regulatory license fee is imposed at a
10 rate of four-tenths of a cent ($0.004) for each milliliter of alcohol contained in an
11 alcoholic beverage for human consumption sold, used, or distributed by sale or
12 gift in the Commonwealth of Kentucky on every:
13 (a) Wholesaler;
14 (b) Distributor;
15 (c) Distiller that directly transfers products to its retail premises;
