1 SECTION 5. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 217 IS CREATED TO
2 READ AS FOLLOWS:
3 (1) As used in this section:
4 (a) "Certified reference materials" means highly accurate, stable, and
5 homogenous substances with documented traceability to SI units, used to
6 evaluate methods and to ensure measurement quality;
7 (b) "Department" means the Department for Public Health;
8 (c) "Fit-for-purpose" means a validated test procedure that is suitable,
9 functional, and effective for its intended use and meets required standards;
10 (d) "Proficiency test" means a test established to evaluate the ability of a
11 laboratory to perform test procedures required under this section by
12 comparing each laboratory’s results against a set of standards;
13 (e) "Proficiency test sample" means an unknown substance sent by an
14 approved, external provider to a laboratory for analysis to evaluate
15 accuracy, precision, and performance. Proficiency test samples are
16 submitted blindly for testing using the same methods as are used for
17 regular, routine samples to assess the ability of the laboratory to produce
18 valid results; and
19 (f) "Third-party laboratory" means an independent, impartial testing entity not
20 affiliated with a manufacturer, wholesaler, retailer, or any other seller or
21 buyer of a hemp-derived cannabinoid product.
22 (2) The department shall work to improve testing procedures, proficiency testing, and
23 approvals of third-party laboratories who seek to test registered hemp-derived
24 cannabinoid products for sale in Kentucky.
25 (3) Third-party laboratories certified to test registered hemp-derived cannabinoid
26 products shall meet the following requirements:
27 (a) Accreditation under ISO/IEC 17025:2017 standard by an ISO-certified
Page 15 of 109
XXXX 3/4/2026 4:40 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 323
1 accreditation body, including accreditation for each method used for testing
2 hemp-derived cannabinoid products;
3 (b) Comprehensive quality systems and validated methods for testing hemp-
4 derived cannabinoids using both Gas Chromatography-Mass Spectrometry
5 (GC-MS/ or GC-MS/MS) and High-Performance Liquid Chromatography
6 (HPLC-PDA or LC-MS/MS) systems;
7 (c) Establishing standard operating procedures and methodologies for testing
8 products containing hemp-derived cannabinoids that are fit-for-purpose;
9 (d) Utilizing fit-for-purpose testing for plant material, oils, edibles, beverages,
10 and vaporizable products;
11 (e) Participating in an accredited proficiency testing program under ISO/IEC
12 17043; and
13 (f) Meeting other standards necessary to fulfill the requirements of this section.
14 (4) (a) The department shall establish a proficiency test for demonstrating
15 proficiency in testing hemp-derived cannabinoids for the purpose of
16 evaluating and approving third-party laboratories that seek to conduct
17 compliance testing of hemp-derived cannabinoid products registered in the
18 Commonwealth.
19 (b) The department shall establish the proficiency test. The department shall
20 utilize certified reference materials to create a reference product for
21 compliance testing. The reference product shall include the following
22 cannabinoids:
23 1. Cannabidiol (CBD) (CAS # 13956-29-1);
24 2. Cannabinol (CBN) (CAS # 521-35-7);
25 3. Delta-9-tetrahydrocannabinolic acid (THCA) (CAS # 23978-85-0);
26 4. Delta-9-tetrahydrocannabinol (delta-9-THC) (CAS # 1972-08-3);
27 5. Delta-8-tetrahydrocannabinol (delta-8-THC) (CAS # 5757-75-5);
