12 (5) Upon establishing the proficiency test, the department shall establish an approval
13 process for third-party laboratories seeking to conduct testing of hemp-derived
14 cannabinoid products intended for registration in the Commonwealth in
15 accordance with the following:
16 (a) The department shall provide proficiency test materials to any third-party
17 laboratory that seeks approval to conduct cannabinoid testing for hemp-
18 derived cannabinoid products intended for registration in Kentucky;
19 (b) Participating third-party laboratories shall test each proficiency sample
20 using the validated methods and analytical procedures that are within their
21 scope of accreditation as specified on their accreditation certificate and
22 submit their results to the department within a timeframe established by the
23 department;
24 (c) The department shall compare the proficiency test results submitted by
25 third-party laboratories to target values and to the results derived from the
26 same reference materials by other certified laboratories. The results from
