1 computer software access services purchased from a retailer.
2 (b) "Storage" does not include the keeping, retaining, or exercising any right or
3 power over tangible personal property for the purpose of subsequently
4 transporting it outside the state for use thereafter solely outside the state, or
5 for the purpose of being processed, fabricated, or manufactured into, attached
6 to, or incorporated into, other tangible personal property to be transported
7 outside the state and thereafter used solely outside the state;
8 (46) "Tangible personal property" means personal property which may be seen,
9 weighed, measured, felt, or touched, or which is in any other manner perceptible to
10 the senses and includes natural, artificial, and mixed gas, electricity, water, steam,
11 and prewritten computer software;
12 (47) "Taxpayer" means any person liable for tax under this chapter;
13 (48) "Telemarketing services" means services provided via telephone, facsimile,
14 electronic mail, text messages, or other modes of communications to another
15 person, which are unsolicited by that person, for the purposes of:
16 (a) 1. Promoting products or services;
17 2. Taking orders; or
18 3. Providing information or assistance regarding the products or services;
19 or
20 (b) Soliciting contributions;
21 (49) "Transferred electronically" means accessed or obtained by the purchaser by means
22 other than tangible storage media; and
