18 Section 32. KRS 243.045 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) A transitional license may be issued by the state administrator or administrators
20 during the time a transfer of an ongoing business is being processed under the
21 following conditions:
22 (a) The purchaser shall file an application for a permanent license with the
23 appropriate local alcoholic beverage authority and with the department;
24 (b) The purchaser shall submit its license application to the department for
25 placement on the department's online listing[advertise its intention to apply
26 for a license] pursuant to KRS 243.360; and
27 (c) The purchaser shall pay all application fees for the permanent license.
Page 103 of 109
XXXX 3/4/2026 4:40 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 323
1 (2) If the above requirements are met, the state administrator or administrators, as
2 appropriate, may issue a transitional license with a term of up to sixty (60) days,
3 plus one (1) thirty (30) day renewal license, to the purchaser for a processing fee set
4 forth in KRS 243.030 to 243.040. All transitional licenses immediately expire upon
5 the issuance to the purchaser of one (1) or more permanent licenses.
6 (3) Upon completion of the sale of the business, the purchaser shall not operate the
7 business on the seller's license.
8 (4) The transitional license shall not be transferable or used for an application to move
9 a business from one (1) location to another location.
10 (5) The transitional license shall entitle the holder to the same privileges and
11 restrictions of the permanent license or licenses for which the holder applied under
12 subsection (1)(a) of this section.
13 Section 33. KRS 243.430 is amended to read as follows:
14 (1) The state administrator may deny any application for a license if the application is
15 incomplete or the correct fee has not been remitted with the application.
16 (2) A license shall not be approved or issued until the fourteen (14)[thirty (30)] day
17 period in which a protest is permissible has expired. Any license for which
18 department listing[public notice] under KRS 243.360 is required may conditionally
19 be issued in less than fourteen (14)[thirty (30)] days from the date the application is
20 received if the premises has previously operated under the same type of license
21 within the last twelve (12) months.
22 (3) The state administrator shall deny, approve, or issue licenses when, in the sound
23 discretion of the administrator, all of the information necessary has been obtained
24 or the applicant has refused to provide requested information.
