2 Section 36. KRS 243.990 is amended to read as follows:
3 (1) Any person who, by himself or herself or acting through another, directly or
4 indirectly, violates any of the provisions of KRS 243.020 to 243.670, for which no
5 other penalty is provided, shall, for the first offense, be guilty of a Class B
6 misdemeanor; and for the second and each subsequent violation, he or she shall be
7 guilty of a Class A misdemeanor. The penalties provided for in this subsection shall
8 be in addition to the revocation of the offender's license.
9 (2) Any person who, by himself or herself or through another, directly or indirectly,
10 violates subsection (1) of KRS 243.020 shall, for the first offense, be guilty of a
11 Class B misdemeanor; for the second offense, he or she shall be guilty of a Class A
12 misdemeanor; and for the third and each subsequent offense, he or she shall be
13 guilty of a Class D felony.
14 (3) Any person who violates subsection (3) of KRS 243.020 shall be guilty of a
15 violation.
16 (4) Any person who violates KRS 243.620 with respect to a license issued under KRS
17 243.050 or 243.082 shall be guilty of a violation.
18 (5) Any person who violates any of the provisions of Section 2 of this Act[KRS
19 243.720 or 243.730] or any administrative regulation issued thereunder shall be
20 guilty of a Class A misdemeanor.
21 (6) Any person who violates any provision of Section 2 of this Act[KRS 243.710 to
22 243.850] shall be subject to the uniform civil penalties imposed pursuant to KRS
23 131.180.
24 (7) In every case, any state wholesale regulatory license fee[tax] imposed by Section 2
25 of this Act[KRS 243.710 to 243.720] which is not paid on or before the due date
26 shall bear interest at the tax interest rate as defined in KRS 131.010(6) from the due
27 date until the date of payment.
